{"questionId":"9066616","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">This question is about antiviral drugs.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Oseltamivir, used for the treatment of severe flu, is inactive until converted in the liver to its active carboxylate form.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Draw a circle around the functional group that can be converted to the carboxylate by hydrolysis.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/131979b38a60babaeb963e45e0673677d6e8562c.png\" width=\"407\" height=\"286\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/7868710260c100d3eea44321142b9f2a4ee1d1e3.png\"> &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔]</span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Note:&nbsp;</span></strong></em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Accept circles that include the alkyl side</em> chain.</span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066616","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ1.22a(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw a circle around the functional group that can be converted to the carboxylate by hydrolysis.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.5 Anti-viral medications","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}